Class FeedList

  • java.lang.Object
    • android.support.v4.app.Fragment
      • com.realestate.custom.CustomFragment

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.content.ComponentCallbacks, android.view.View.OnClickListener, android.view.View.OnCreateContextMenuListener

    public class FeedList
extends CustomFragment
    The Class FeedList is the Fragment class that is launched when the user clicks on Feed option in Left navigation drawer and this is also used as a default fragment for MainActivity. It simply shows a dummy list of Property Feeds. You can customize this class to display actual Feed listing.
